            <div type="commentary" resp="#martaf">
                <p>The fragment was probably part of an epitaph: the traces at l. 3 could be part of the dedication verb <foreign xml:lang="grc">ποιέω</foreign>, as Korhonen hypothesised. The interpunct could divide the first sentence with the name of the deceased and his age, from the second sentence with the name of the dedicant and the dedication verb, in this case in the first position as in IG 14.467 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001291">ISic001291</ref>, where an interpunct also divides the two sentences.</p>
            </div>
